it has been suggested that pushyamitra may have destroyed the original stupa , and his son agnimitra rebuilt it."who was responsible for the wanton destruction of the original brick stupa of ashoka and when precisely the great work of reconstruction was carried out is not known , but it seems probable that the author of the former was pushyamitra , the first of the shunga kings ( 184 - 148 bc ) , who was notorious for his hostility to buddhism , and that the restoration was affected by agnimitra or his immediate successor . " in john marshall , a guide to sanchi , p. 38 .

